                                      \r\n                                                                                                          \r\n\u001b[38;5;239m\u001b[48;5;237mвқҜ \u001b[38;5;231mYou are the LEAD orchestrator. You work in /home/sdb with one Worker (worker1) and one Tester \u001b[39m          \r\n  \u001b[38;5;231m(tester1), each running in its own pane. Read your playbook at \u001b[39m                                         \r\n  \u001b[38;5;231m/home/sdb/.local/share/claude-team/team/ORCHESTRATION.md now, then use \u001b[39m                                 \r\n  \u001b[38;5;231m/home/sdb/.local/share/claude-team/team/team.sh to dispatch to agents BY NAME (e.g. worker1, worker2, \u001b[39m  \r\n  \u001b[38;5;231mtester1) with send/sendf/read/check/wait, and put task files under \u001b[39m                                     \r\n  \u001b[38;5;231m/home/sdb/.local/share/claude-team/team/.team/tasks/. Run tasks in parallel across workers only when \u001b[39m   \r\n  \u001b[38;5;231mthey touch DIFFERENT files. After reading, reply READY and wait for my instructions.\u001b[39m                    \r\n\u001b[49m                                                                                                          \r\n\u001b[38;5;231mв—Ҹ\u001b[39m I'll read my orchestration playbook first.                                                              \r\n                                                                                                          \r\n  \u001b[38;5;246mRead \u001b[1m1\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;5;246m file \u001b[39m                                                                                            \r\n                                                                                                          \r\n\u001b[38;5;231mв—Ҹ\u001b[39m READY                                                                                                   \r\n                                                                     